cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the problem of estimating deep generative language models using variational inference and deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses techniques related to machine learning and optimization, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of deep neural networks suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks for image processing, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for hierarchical probabilistic models, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
